.TH DRACHMA-QT 1 "January 2026" "drachma 0.1.0" "DRACHMA Core"
.SH NAME
drachma-qt \- DRACHMA graphical user interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B drachma-qt
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B drachma-qt
provides a Qt-based graphical user interface for the DRACHMA cryptocurrency. 
It integrates a wallet, block explorer, and network connectivity in a single application.
.PP
The DRACHMA wallet provides multi-asset support (TLN, DRM, OBL), NFT gallery, 
smart contract interaction, and dApp browsing capabilities.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-conf=\fIFILE\fR
Specify configuration file (default: drachma.conf)
.TP
.BR \-datadir=\fIDIR\fR
Specify data directory
.TP
.BR \-network=\fINETWORK\fR
Connect to network (mainnet, testnet, regtest)
.TP
.BR \-connect=\fIIP:PORT\fR
Connect to a DRACHMA node at IP:PORT
.TP
.BR \-min
Start minimized
.TP
.BR \-resetguisettings
Reset all settings changed in the GUI
.TP
.BR \-version
Print version and exit
.TP
.BR \-help
Print help message and exit
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Wallet Management
Send and receive DRM, TLN, and OBL tokens
.TP
.B NFT Gallery
View, mint, and trade NFTs on the Layer 2 sidechain
.TP
.B Smart Contracts
Deploy and interact with WASM smart contracts
.TP
.B dApp Browser
Access decentralized applications built on DRACHMA
.TP
.B Transaction History
View detailed transaction history with filtering options
.TP
.B Address Book
Manage contacts and frequently used addresses
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.drachma/drachma.conf
Configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.drachma/wallet.dat
Wallet data file
.TP
.I ~/.drachma/peers.dat
Peer address database
